The paper deals with a novel algorithm for solving learning problems with non-convex loss functions and regularizers. This is a common problem in machine learning and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves numerical optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves experiments on high-dimensional data, which can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with transductive learning, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves experiments on image data, which can be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
